{"title": "Red Arrows in the Night", "description": "The Scarlet Archer of Agincourt is claimed by the Erkenwold\u2019s as their family ghost. Tradition held that the death of an important Erkenwold was always heralded by the apparition of the Scarlet Archer. Now in the early years of WWII, the archer has made an appearance on the family estate on the US coast. Is it a ghost or something more sinister, and what does he or she want?<br><br>This mystery novel was written by Daniel A Lord, S.J., who was a popular American Catholic writer. The subjects of the works in his bibliography range from religion, humor, plays, songs, mysteries and even politics. His most influential work was possibly in drafting the 1930 Production Code for motion pictures. (Introduction by Maria Therese and Wikipedia)", "duration": 13813, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "1443", "name": "Daniel A. Lord"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCovers3/red_arrows_1011.jpg", "copyright_year": "1943", "genres": ["Detective Fiction", "Religious Fiction"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Maria Therese"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Maria Therese"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Barry Eads"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Elli"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "1 - Chapter 1", "readers": [4667], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/red_arrows_in_night_1011_librivox/redarrowsinnight_1_lord_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1724}, {"section": 2, "title": "2 - Chapter 2", "readers": [4667], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/red_arrows_in_night_1011_librivox/redarrowsinnight_2_lord_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1534}, {"section": 3, "title": "3 - Chapter 3", "readers": [4667], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/red_arrows_in_night_1011_librivox/redarrowsinnight_3_lord_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1596}, {"section": 4, "title": "4 - Chapter 4", "readers": [4667], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/red_arrows_in_night_1011_librivox/r